Chile Government Says It’s More Optimistic About Power Supply After Rains

-- B y   M a t t h e w   C r a z e
-- 
2011-05-03T13:03:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/chile-government-says-it-s-more-optimistic-about-power-supply-after-rains.html
     May 3 (Bloomberg) -- Chile ’s government is more optimistic
about electricity supply after recent rains in the country’s
south, Mining and Energy Minister  Laurence Golborne  said today.  Measures to prevent energy rationing remain in place after
dry weather had limited hydroelectricity generation, Golborne
told reporters today at a conference in Santiago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Craze in Santiago at 
